      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a mechanically sound driver\u2019s car featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine and a precise 6-speed G96 manual transaxle. The powertrain delivers linear torque across the rev range, supported by a dual-row ceramic IMS bearing upgrade and a recently inspected rear main seal. The suspension has been tightened with Bilstein B6 dampers and fresh polyurethane bushings, ensuring the chassis remains communicative during high-lateral-G cornering. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the drivetrain is robust, with a clean DME report and no evidence of bore scoring. It sits on factory staggered 18-inch Carrera lightweight alloys wrapped in N-spec rubber, ready for spirited canyon carving or track-day duty.",
